<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-607-648  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 607 648.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Information Week  Sept 4 1989 n235 p28(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>The trouble with storage. (automation provides solutions tostorage problems)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Colonna, Jerome D.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The automation of data storage has reduced problems associatedwith managing storage devices such as data center personnelinefficiency and space shortage.andP;  Among the storage toolsavailable are: Storage Technology Corp's 4400 Automatic CartridgeSystem (ACS) for IBM 3480-compatible tape cartridges and MemorexTelex's 5400 Automatic Tape Library (ATL).andP;  Both products userobotic technology to file and locate cartridges.andP;  ACS consists ofup to 16 library storage modules and can store up to 1,600Gbytesof data.andP;  ATL, which can hold up to 1,030Gbytes of non-compresseddata and up to 2Tbytes compressed, includes library managementsoftware that allows data compression.andP;  Despite storage solutionspresented by new technology, there is a need for the applicationof expert system technology to link individual hardware andsoftware tools, combined with links to other data centerautomation tools.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     AutomationMISMass MemoryPerformance ImprovementRobotsPersonnel ManagementExpert SystemsStorage Capacity.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>